WHAT IS TAF ?
› A frame work that provides full end to end test case
automation
› Test design
› Test execution
› Test reporting
› Test case architecture to foster reusable components in
and between teams
› Suggested class structure to enable easier maintenance,
tool abstraction, consistent approach

Ericsson Internal | 2013-02-20 | Page 6
Taf re-use
TAF Goal : Provide Building Blocks for re-useable automated tests
for functional & performance tests
Test Steps
• A reusable method
• A test action and can contain verification of output of the
action
• Can have own Test Data Source
• Available in TAF Registry – source for all shared test code
Flows
• A flow is an ordered list of test steps
• Flows can be executed in series or parallel
• Flows can over write Test Step Test Data
Scenario
• A series of test steps organized into flows
• Re-useable for Functional testing to Performance and End-to
-end workflow testing
